1
00:00:06,606 --> 00:00:08,407
(BELL TOLLING)

2
00:00:11,611 --> 00:00:17,083
RIDDLER: <i>Riddle me this.
When is a door, not a door?</i>

3
00:00:17,084 --> 00:00:19,219
<i>It feels like drowning, doesn't it?</i>

4
00:00:19,220 --> 00:00:22,022
<i>When the answer is at the
edge of your cortex,</i>

5
00:00:22,023 --> 00:00:25,492
<i>but you can't seem to grasp it.</i>

6
00:00:25,493 --> 00:00:27,360
AMANDA: <i>You're trying my patience.</i>

7
00:00:27,361 --> 00:00:30,762
RIDDLER: <i>The answer...
When it's Ajar!</i>

8
00:00:31,898 --> 00:00:33,299
<i>Here is an easy one.</i>

9
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:37,502
<i>What runs around a
city, but never moves?</i>

10
00:00:37,737 --> 00:00:38,872
No?

11
00:00:38,873 --> 00:00:40,505
A wall!

12
00:00:41,274 --> 00:00:44,310
<i>What do you want, Nigma?</i>

13
00:00:44,311 --> 00:00:47,180
I'm in charge so I'll
ask the questions.

14
00:00:47,181 --> 00:00:48,581
Try to keep up, wont you?

15
00:00:48,582 --> 00:00:50,617
Riddle me this.
What belongs to you,

16
00:00:50,618 --> 00:00:53,753
but others use it more than you do?

17
00:00:53,754 --> 00:00:55,055
AMANDA: <i>Your name.</i>

18
00:00:55,056 --> 00:00:56,389
Huh!

19
00:00:56,390 --> 00:00:57,724
You've heard that one!

20
00:00:57,725 --> 00:00:59,926
No, I have Google,

21
00:00:59,927 --> 00:01:02,662
like the rest of the world.

22
00:01:02,663 --> 00:01:05,465
<i>Why do you talk to me
like this, waller?</i>

23
00:01:05,466 --> 00:01:08,068
Simple, I needed to
keep you babbling

24
00:01:08,069 --> 00:01:10,236
long enough to pinpoint
your position.

25
00:01:10,237 --> 00:01:11,770
My... what?

26
00:01:18,545 --> 00:01:21,580
OFFICER: Hands in the air,
where we can see them!

27
00:01:23,416 --> 00:01:25,118
AMANDA: <i>Take him out!</i>

28
00:01:25,119 --> 00:01:26,885
Make it hurt!

29
00:01:27,787 --> 00:01:29,321
(GRUNTS)

30
00:01:30,023 --> 00:01:31,357
Riddle me this.

31
00:01:31,358 --> 00:01:33,925
Why didn't I quit when I was ahead?

32
00:01:38,765 --> 00:01:40,565
What is it? Report!

33
00:01:43,069 --> 00:01:45,138
BATMAN: The riddler is mine!

34
00:01:45,139 --> 00:01:46,872
OFFICER: Switch to night vision!

35
00:01:48,208 --> 00:01:49,941
Secure the perimeter!

36
00:01:54,013 --> 00:01:56,014
Holy crap! It's Batman!

37
00:01:56,382 --> 00:01:57,649
(GRUNTS)

38
00:02:00,053 --> 00:02:01,687
(OFFICERS GRUNTING)

39
00:02:06,926 --> 00:02:08,527
(PROJECTILE SWISHING)

40
00:02:37,123 --> 00:02:38,724
RIDDLER: Ahh!

41
00:02:41,895 --> 00:02:43,362
(BOTH GRUNTS)

42
00:02:48,268 --> 00:02:49,735
(GROWLING)

43
00:02:54,707 --> 00:02:55,974
(STRAINING)

44
00:03:07,086 --> 00:03:08,454
(PANTING)

45
00:03:08,455 --> 00:03:09,721
(GROANS)

46
00:03:24,737 --> 00:03:26,004
(STRAINING)

47
00:03:26,973 --> 00:03:29,108
I know you helped him, Nigma.

48
00:03:29,109 --> 00:03:31,576
Tell me where it is.

49
00:03:34,747 --> 00:03:35,882
(BUZZER BEEPS)

50
00:03:35,883 --> 00:03:38,985
I'm invoking priority
level, ultraviolet.

51
00:03:38,986 --> 00:03:41,454
Assemble task force X.

52
00:03:41,455 --> 00:03:43,822
We have another suicide mission.

53
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:47,159
(DUBSTEP PLAYING)

54
00:04:46,986 --> 00:04:48,620
(PRISONERS CHEERING)

55
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:55,160
(MOTORBIKE ENGINE REVVING)

56
00:05:37,337 --> 00:05:38,803
(ALARM RINGS)

57
00:06:03,296 --> 00:06:04,763
(GRUNTS)

58
00:06:42,034 --> 00:06:43,301
(ALL GROANING)

59
00:06:49,675 --> 00:06:54,180
CAPTAIN BOOMERANG: I got the hangover,
but I don't recall the party.

60
00:06:54,181 --> 00:06:57,282
Oh crap! Not this again!

61
00:06:58,050 --> 00:06:59,152
You too?

62
00:06:59,153 --> 00:07:01,587
It's like a bloody
recurring nightmare.

63
00:07:01,588 --> 00:07:03,256
Looks like we've got rookies.

64
00:07:03,257 --> 00:07:04,889
(GROANING)

65
00:07:07,393 --> 00:07:09,028
Who are you people?

66
00:07:09,029 --> 00:07:11,097
And why am I in uniform?

67
00:07:11,098 --> 00:07:12,498
No bars!

68
00:07:12,499 --> 00:07:14,267
No chains!

69
00:07:14,268 --> 00:07:16,401
Time for meat!

70
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:18,171
(SQUEALS)

71
00:07:18,172 --> 00:07:19,638
Ow!

72
00:07:22,208 --> 00:07:26,212
You try it, fish fingers, and I'll
show you the meaning of cold-blooded.

73
00:07:26,213 --> 00:07:28,247
You're feisty.

74
00:07:28,248 --> 00:07:30,917
Everybody! Shut up!

75
00:07:30,918 --> 00:07:33,118
- I've been here before.
- (SHOUTING)

76
00:07:36,255 --> 00:07:37,490
(GROWLS)

77
00:07:37,491 --> 00:07:38,990
I am leaving!

78
00:07:39,225 --> 00:07:40,692
Stop!

79
00:07:42,495 --> 00:07:44,195
Sit down!

80
00:07:50,102 --> 00:07:51,737
I'm Amanda waller.

81
00:07:51,738 --> 00:07:55,907
I'm here to indoctrinate you
convicts into our special forces.

82
00:07:56,576 --> 00:07:58,043
KILLER FROST: Pass.

83
00:07:58,945 --> 00:08:01,781
I kill to keep degenerates
off the streets.

84
00:08:01,782 --> 00:08:04,817
I won't work alongside them.

85
00:08:04,818 --> 00:08:06,986
Fresh air and term off my sentence?

86
00:08:06,987 --> 00:08:09,822
Feel free to keep
calling me up, love.

87
00:08:09,823 --> 00:08:13,793
Task force X is an off-the-books
government strike team,

88
00:08:13,794 --> 00:08:16,529
made up of convicts with
no hope for release,

89
00:08:16,530 --> 00:08:18,731
serving as expendable agents,

90
00:08:18,732 --> 00:08:20,732
for impossible missions.

91
00:08:21,901 --> 00:08:26,138
Succeed, and I'll shave
time off your sentences.

92
00:08:26,139 --> 00:08:27,772
If we don't?

93
00:08:28,140 --> 00:08:29,375
You'll be dead!

94
00:08:29,376 --> 00:08:31,744
Any other stupid questions?

95
00:08:31,745 --> 00:08:34,947
Yeah, what's in my neck? A tracker?

96
00:08:34,948 --> 00:08:39,051
Yes, and a powerful
nanotech explosive.

97
00:08:39,052 --> 00:08:41,587
Run away, get yourself captured,

98
00:08:41,588 --> 00:08:43,089
disobey an order,

99
00:08:43,090 --> 00:08:45,958
hell, give me a right
answer too slowly,

100
00:08:45,959 --> 00:08:49,461
and I'll blow your head clean off!

101
00:08:50,830 --> 00:08:52,864
KGBEAST: You're lying.

102
00:08:54,333 --> 00:08:58,770
You would not take all of this
trouble, just to kill us.

103
00:09:03,209 --> 00:09:04,743
Try me!

104
00:09:19,492 --> 00:09:21,025
(BEEPING)

105
00:09:22,662 --> 00:09:24,129
(SCREAMS)

106
00:09:29,201 --> 00:09:31,102
Anyone else?

107
00:09:32,371 --> 00:09:34,707
I didn't think so.

108
00:09:34,708 --> 00:09:39,779
What's so dangerous this time that
you had to send in the newbies?

109
00:09:39,780 --> 00:09:42,514
You're going to break
into Arkham asylum.

110
00:09:43,683 --> 00:09:45,384
- That's insane!
- You don't know much, do you?

111
00:09:45,385 --> 00:09:46,586
Screw that!

112
00:09:46,587 --> 00:09:47,987
I don't do freaky deaky's.

113
00:09:47,988 --> 00:09:49,589
Yahtzee!

114
00:09:49,590 --> 00:09:51,222
How do we start?

115
00:09:52,425 --> 00:09:55,695
Oh, I like you, cowboy.

116
00:09:55,696 --> 00:09:57,063
You're <i>loco!</i>

117
00:09:57,064 --> 00:10:00,800
And me likey your locomotion!

118
00:10:00,801 --> 00:10:02,568
- Ahh!
- What's the plan?

119
00:10:02,569 --> 00:10:04,770
A week ago, while in my employ,

120
00:10:04,771 --> 00:10:09,709
a low life calling himself the riddler managed
to gain access to my computer system.

121
00:10:09,710 --> 00:10:12,144
He downloaded a file
containing the identities

122
00:10:12,145 --> 00:10:17,882
and histories of every current, past and
potential member of the suicide squad.

123
00:10:18,217 --> 00:10:19,685
Including ours?

124
00:10:19,686 --> 00:10:21,253
That's right!

125
00:10:21,254 --> 00:10:23,956
He's threatening to release
them all on the Internet.

126
00:10:23,957 --> 00:10:26,492
You're going to get it back.

127
00:10:26,493 --> 00:10:28,094
Riddler's got one copy,

128
00:10:28,095 --> 00:10:30,262
and it's on a thumb
drive in his cane,

129
00:10:30,263 --> 00:10:33,799
which is apparently locked away
in the Arkham property room.

130
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:39,105
In the intensive treatment building, right
under the solitary confinement cells.

131
00:10:39,106 --> 00:10:40,473
Good times!

132
00:10:40,474 --> 00:10:41,841
So we get someone inside.

133
00:10:41,842 --> 00:10:44,176
Is it me? Can it be me?

134
00:10:44,177 --> 00:10:45,543
Dibs!

135
00:10:45,911 --> 00:10:47,713
She's a wild card.

136
00:10:47,714 --> 00:10:51,450
Harley Quinn, has an encyclopedic
knowledge of Arkham's layout

137
00:10:51,451 --> 00:10:52,952
and its logistics.

138
00:10:52,953 --> 00:10:55,520
She gonna be okay that
close to the joker?

139
00:10:56,389 --> 00:10:58,791
I'm fine, we're done.

140
00:10:58,792 --> 00:11:01,626
He's a jerk! Whatever.

141
00:11:03,362 --> 00:11:05,096
Well, I'm convinced.

142
00:11:06,565 --> 00:11:08,601
You'll be snuck into Gotham.

143
00:11:08,602 --> 00:11:12,203
You'll rendezvous with a power broker
who will set you up for the break in.

144
00:11:14,473 --> 00:11:16,108
This is as off-the-grid as it gets.

145
00:11:16,109 --> 00:11:19,412
So let's keep the body
count to a minimum.

146
00:11:19,413 --> 00:11:21,579
Deadshot, rubber bullets only.

147
00:11:22,415 --> 00:11:24,082
What about the bat?

148
00:11:25,985 --> 00:11:28,320
He has his hands full
on another case.

149
00:11:28,321 --> 00:11:32,457
In fact, we work it right, we might
be able to take advantage of him.

150
00:11:34,193 --> 00:11:35,428
Waller!

151
00:11:35,429 --> 00:11:37,029
What, Lawton?

152
00:11:37,030 --> 00:11:39,598
Play fair and I'll shoot straight.

153
00:11:39,599 --> 00:11:41,666
Jerk me around and I'll kill you!

154
00:11:44,737 --> 00:11:47,573
Be a good convict, Lawton.

155
00:11:47,574 --> 00:11:49,507
Don't make me blow you up.

156
00:11:50,676 --> 00:11:52,411
I'm clear!

157
00:11:52,412 --> 00:11:53,546
Gas them!

158
00:11:53,547 --> 00:11:54,613
Harley: What?

159
00:11:54,614 --> 00:11:56,080
(GAS HISSING)

160
00:12:09,662 --> 00:12:11,129
(STRAINING)

161
00:12:12,164 --> 00:12:14,834
I'm getting tired of this trick.

162
00:12:14,835 --> 00:12:17,470
You and me both, cowboy.

163
00:12:17,471 --> 00:12:21,807
Maybe, when we get into Gotham,
I can show you around.

164
00:12:21,808 --> 00:12:24,677
I know some tight places.

165
00:12:24,678 --> 00:12:26,579
- Not interested.
- Hmm.

166
00:12:26,580 --> 00:12:28,948
I told you Harley,

167
00:12:28,949 --> 00:12:32,550
if you're giving it out,
heave a chunk my way, eh.

168
00:12:32,952 --> 00:12:34,820
Eh! You wish!

169
00:12:34,821 --> 00:12:37,356
Shake your boomerang
at the shark guy.

170
00:12:37,357 --> 00:12:41,025
- Do it, and I will bite it off.
- (CHUCKLES)

171
00:12:45,064 --> 00:12:48,566
Come on, Harl, for old times' sake!

172
00:12:49,468 --> 00:12:51,837
Are we gonna have a
problem this time around?

173
00:12:51,838 --> 00:12:53,672
I think we might, mate.

174
00:12:53,673 --> 00:12:55,508
BLACK SPIDER: No!

175
00:12:55,509 --> 00:12:56,709
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

176
00:12:56,710 --> 00:12:58,177
I don't trust vermin.

177
00:12:58,178 --> 00:13:02,114
Honorless, rudderless,
undisciplined.

178
00:13:02,115 --> 00:13:05,151
They'll never find your body.

179
00:13:05,152 --> 00:13:08,152
Harley: Oh, ninjas are awesome!

180
00:13:11,390 --> 00:13:12,657
(GRUNTS)

181
00:13:20,866 --> 00:13:23,267
You think that means we're there?

182
00:13:26,839 --> 00:13:28,306
(ALL SCREAM)

183
00:13:29,108 --> 00:13:32,176
KING SHARK: I hate heights!

184
00:13:32,545 --> 00:13:34,178
(STRAINING)

185
00:13:39,585 --> 00:13:41,252
(Harley LAUGHING)

186
00:13:41,620 --> 00:13:43,022
Harley: Whoo!

187
00:13:43,023 --> 00:13:44,523
We're not going to make it!

188
00:13:44,524 --> 00:13:46,091
Waller, please!

189
00:13:46,092 --> 00:13:47,493
Ahh!

190
00:13:47,494 --> 00:13:49,728
(CACKLING)

191
00:13:49,729 --> 00:13:54,400
AMANDA: <i>Remember this feeling convicts,
I hold your lives in my hands!</i>

192
00:13:54,401 --> 00:13:56,468
You crazy bitch!

193
00:13:56,469 --> 00:13:57,803
Open the damn chutes!

194
00:13:57,804 --> 00:13:59,570
Do it, now!

195
00:14:01,707 --> 00:14:03,241
(ALL SCREAMING)

196
00:14:07,513 --> 00:14:08,780
(SCREAMS)

197
00:14:28,067 --> 00:14:31,502
Good one! Good shark!

198
00:14:31,871 --> 00:14:33,504
Oh, Christ!

199
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:36,107
Where's Harley?

200
00:14:38,210 --> 00:14:41,446
Don't worry! I fell on my head.

201
00:14:45,217 --> 00:14:48,319
Great! Now, how do we get
to the rendezvous unseen?

202
00:14:56,395 --> 00:14:57,930
A few more Miles.

203
00:14:57,931 --> 00:14:59,597
Keep moving, then.

204
00:14:59,865 --> 00:15:01,365
(GROANING)

205
00:15:06,639 --> 00:15:07,806
(EXCLAIMS)

206
00:15:07,807 --> 00:15:09,575
This is flipping bonkers!

207
00:15:09,576 --> 00:15:12,711
Sloshing through the sewage so a guy
dressed like a bat won't spot us.

208
00:15:12,712 --> 00:15:14,712
You want to head top side, slick?

209
00:15:14,980 --> 00:15:16,781
Be my guest!

210
00:15:21,754 --> 00:15:24,290
Nah! We're practically there.

211
00:15:24,291 --> 00:15:26,624
Yeah, that's what I thought.

212
00:15:28,894 --> 00:15:31,129
(MUSIC PLAYING IN DISTANCE)

213
00:15:36,535 --> 00:15:37,802
Cobblepot!

214
00:15:39,571 --> 00:15:42,074
MAN: We're closed! Private party!

215
00:15:42,075 --> 00:15:44,475
Yeah, we're the private party!

216
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:52,184
This way. He's waiting on you.

217
00:15:52,185 --> 00:15:55,120
Your guests have
arrived, Mr. Cobblepot.

218
00:15:55,121 --> 00:15:57,289
Right, right. Come in!

219
00:15:57,290 --> 00:15:59,058
Welcome to the iceberg lounge.

220
00:15:59,059 --> 00:16:00,858
I'm just finishing my supper.

221
00:16:11,971 --> 00:16:14,340
Pardon me, Mr. Cobblepot.

222
00:16:14,341 --> 00:16:19,044
Lawton. Oh, I never pegged
Deadshot for a team player.

223
00:16:19,045 --> 00:16:21,479
Oh, things are tough all over, sir.

224
00:16:24,783 --> 00:16:27,152
That's a good one!

225
00:16:27,153 --> 00:16:30,155
This man is the best
assassin I've ever seen.

226
00:16:30,156 --> 00:16:32,458
And I only work with the best.

227
00:16:32,459 --> 00:16:35,127
I aim to please, Mr. Cobblepot.

228
00:16:35,128 --> 00:16:37,663
I was told you can
get us into Arkham.

229
00:16:37,664 --> 00:16:39,264
I can, indeed.

230
00:16:39,265 --> 00:16:42,167
I've made arrangements to sneak
you into the crazy farm.

231
00:16:42,168 --> 00:16:43,669
Follow them to...

232
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:44,936
You!

233
00:16:45,337 --> 00:16:46,737
Clown!

234
00:16:47,973 --> 00:16:51,943
You're still not mad about
that truck, are you, Pengie?

235
00:16:53,112 --> 00:16:54,579
Wah, wah.

236
00:16:56,015 --> 00:16:58,282
It feels like you are.

237
00:16:59,084 --> 00:17:01,320
You cost me money, funny girl!

238
00:17:01,321 --> 00:17:06,125
Her and her loony boyfriend lit my truck
a cigarette and drove it into the river!

239
00:17:06,126 --> 00:17:07,926
Just for a laugh!

240
00:17:07,927 --> 00:17:11,497
Does it matter that Mr. J and
I aren't together anymore?

241
00:17:11,498 --> 00:17:14,066
Nobody steals from
me and walks away!

242
00:17:14,067 --> 00:17:15,900
It's bad business, love!

243
00:17:17,236 --> 00:17:19,238
You're right, you should kill her!

244
00:17:19,239 --> 00:17:20,973
Hell, I'll kill her for you!

245
00:17:20,974 --> 00:17:22,508
Oh, come on!

246
00:17:22,509 --> 00:17:25,543
Except, you know what else
is bad for business, sir?

247
00:17:27,980 --> 00:17:30,916
Double crossing your clients.

248
00:17:30,917 --> 00:17:34,486
And I would hate for folks to say,
"Mr. Cobblepot takes your money

249
00:17:34,487 --> 00:17:36,020
"and kills your operatives."

250
00:17:39,525 --> 00:17:41,892
Get her out of my sight, Lawton.

251
00:17:44,363 --> 00:17:46,298
There's your files.

252
00:17:46,299 --> 00:17:49,435
Memorize the contents. You can grab
some shut-eye in the rooms above.

253
00:17:49,436 --> 00:17:52,871
You deploy tomorrow night
under the cover of darkness.

254
00:17:52,872 --> 00:17:57,742
And then, I never want to see
any of you on my turf again.

255
00:17:58,310 --> 00:18:00,878
Now, get the hell out of here!

256
00:18:03,549 --> 00:18:05,584
Never the charmer, aren't you?

257
00:18:05,585 --> 00:18:07,051
Bite me, boomer!

258
00:18:43,021 --> 00:18:44,488
(MEN LAUGHING)

259
00:18:50,696 --> 00:18:51,962
Oy, Lawton!

260
00:18:53,165 --> 00:18:54,800
Nice shade, mate.

261
00:18:54,801 --> 00:18:57,336
We got off on the wrong foot
at the start of this mission.

262
00:18:57,337 --> 00:18:59,471
Hoist a pint with us.

263
00:18:59,472 --> 00:19:01,673
Can't, it's a school night.

264
00:19:01,674 --> 00:19:04,942
Suit yourself. How about a
friendly game of darts, then?

265
00:19:13,085 --> 00:19:14,552
ALL: Yeah!

266
00:19:24,096 --> 00:19:25,164
(ALL GASP)

267
00:19:25,165 --> 00:19:26,832
Lucky shot!

268
00:19:26,833 --> 00:19:29,601
Right, let's see you do it.

269
00:19:29,602 --> 00:19:30,868
ALL: Yeah!

270
00:19:34,873 --> 00:19:36,375
Sorry mate.

271
00:19:36,376 --> 00:19:38,676
Looks like that one
took a bad bounce.

272
00:19:43,849 --> 00:19:45,116
Ow!

273
00:19:46,218 --> 00:19:48,853
Let's call it even. Mate.

274
00:19:55,827 --> 00:19:56,895
(MACHINE BEEPS)

275
00:19:56,896 --> 00:19:59,431
AMANDA: <i>Louise, it's Amanda,</i>

276
00:19:59,432 --> 00:20:01,767
<i>I have a special
assignment for you.</i>

277
00:20:01,768 --> 00:20:04,869
<i>Something I'd rather keep
between the two of us.</i>

278
00:20:05,337 --> 00:20:06,937
I'm listening.

279
00:20:21,320 --> 00:20:23,121
Welcome back!

280
00:20:23,122 --> 00:20:25,523
- Did you miss me?
- What do you want?

281
00:20:27,092 --> 00:20:31,762
I got an itch I thought you
could help me scratch, cowboy.

282
00:20:32,631 --> 00:20:33,898
(SCREAMS)

283
00:20:34,733 --> 00:20:37,034
Oh, good start!

284
00:20:38,437 --> 00:20:40,738
Oh, what the hell?

285
00:20:45,911 --> 00:20:47,179
(DEADSHOT GROANS)

286
00:20:47,180 --> 00:20:49,013
(CRASHING AND CLANKING)

287
00:20:53,418 --> 00:20:55,052
Harley: Yahtzee!

288
00:21:02,694 --> 00:21:06,197
Here's my stop.
Wish me luck, cowboy.

289
00:21:14,139 --> 00:21:15,606
Yeah!

290
00:21:19,177 --> 00:21:21,313
(GRUNTS)

291
00:21:21,314 --> 00:21:24,114
There's got to be
one here somewhere.

292
00:21:24,916 --> 00:21:26,118
(STRAINING)

293
00:21:26,119 --> 00:21:28,220
BATMAN: You know where
he put it, don't you?

294
00:21:28,221 --> 00:21:30,122
Uh-oh.

295
00:21:30,123 --> 00:21:32,391
Where is it, Harley?

296
00:21:32,392 --> 00:21:35,192
No idea, what you're talking about.

297
00:21:39,398 --> 00:21:41,733
Answers! Now!

298
00:21:41,734 --> 00:21:43,067
(Harley GRUNTS)

299
00:21:43,368 --> 00:21:45,236
Back off, bats.

300
00:21:52,778 --> 00:21:54,144
(BATMAN GROANS)

301
00:22:00,786 --> 00:22:02,152
<i>Where is it?</i>

302
00:22:02,621 --> 00:22:04,890
What's he talking about?

303
00:22:04,891 --> 00:22:08,058
Who knows what these wankers
get worked up about?

304
00:22:08,493 --> 00:22:11,530
I don't know, I swear.

305
00:22:11,531 --> 00:22:14,566
I'm not firing blind
against the bat.

306
00:22:14,567 --> 00:22:18,203
Waller, what the devil is going on?

307
00:22:18,204 --> 00:22:21,740
<i>You don't get to call me up
and demand answers, Deadshot!</i>

308
00:22:21,741 --> 00:22:24,176
What are they talking about?

309
00:22:24,177 --> 00:22:27,379
<i>Joker stole a dirty bomb and
hid it somewhere in Gotham.</i>

310
00:22:27,380 --> 00:22:32,584
<i>Apparently, it's large enough that the
radiation would kill half the population.</i>

311
00:22:32,585 --> 00:22:35,220
<i>Batman's torn the city
apart trying to find it.</i>

312
00:22:35,221 --> 00:22:38,490
<i>At one point he thought
riddler might know.</i>

313
00:22:38,491 --> 00:22:41,526
The joker has a dirty bomb?

314
00:22:41,527 --> 00:22:43,694
That gives me the chills.

315
00:22:45,163 --> 00:22:47,865
Ice puns? Really?

316
00:22:49,167 --> 00:22:51,303
Waller, this is crap.

317
00:22:51,304 --> 00:22:56,441
<i>I don't care, convict.
Do your job!</i>

318
00:22:56,442 --> 00:23:01,111
Honestly, B man, I don't know where
Mr. J puts half of his stuff.

319
00:23:03,382 --> 00:23:08,052
I just wanted a chatty boo-boo doll
before they went on sale tomorrow.

320
00:23:08,320 --> 00:23:09,887
(SIRENS WAILING)

321
00:23:16,395 --> 00:23:17,928
Get her back to Arkham!

322
00:23:18,563 --> 00:23:20,732
Will do, Batman.

323
00:23:20,733 --> 00:23:23,000
Get in there, you nutty broad.

324
00:23:42,087 --> 00:23:43,687
(CAR BOOT OPENING)

325
00:23:50,362 --> 00:23:51,829
(MUMBLING)

326
00:24:28,834 --> 00:24:32,670
<i>I'm in the middle of lunch.
Now I've got to process this crazy dame?</i>

327
00:24:34,139 --> 00:24:35,906
Crazy, huh?

328
00:24:37,108 --> 00:24:41,112
Why don't I just toss her in
her old cell, and come back.

329
00:24:41,113 --> 00:24:44,516
Yeah, right. I've got like half
a dozen new forms to fill up

330
00:24:44,517 --> 00:24:46,350
before you can even come in.

331
00:24:51,990 --> 00:24:54,858
We got ten minutes
to plant the device.

332
00:25:08,039 --> 00:25:10,408
CAPTAIN BOOMERANG:
Where should I dump her?

333
00:25:10,409 --> 00:25:12,443
Put it through the X-ray machine.

334
00:25:22,687 --> 00:25:25,357
GUARD: Heh, don't get
much deader than that.

335
00:25:25,358 --> 00:25:28,393
This one's cold as ice.

336
00:25:28,394 --> 00:25:32,863
Hey buddy, I got nothing in the
system about accepting a new body.

337
00:25:44,075 --> 00:25:46,009
Yeah! Ha-ha.

338
00:25:49,080 --> 00:25:50,514
(MUFFLED PROTEST)

339
00:25:51,049 --> 00:25:52,316
(THUDDING)

340
00:25:59,958 --> 00:26:01,225
(GRUNTS)

341
00:26:02,494 --> 00:26:04,629
It says, "not found."

342
00:26:04,630 --> 00:26:06,531
I came from inside.

343
00:26:06,532 --> 00:26:07,998
Run it again.

344
00:26:09,668 --> 00:26:10,936
Nah, something's wrong.

345
00:26:10,937 --> 00:26:13,270
I'm gonna to have to get security.

346
00:26:17,175 --> 00:26:20,378
Junction box is up ahead.
So move your ass.

347
00:26:20,379 --> 00:26:21,845
JOKER: Harley!

348
00:26:22,647 --> 00:26:24,882
Is it really you?

349
00:26:26,384 --> 00:26:27,786
Shit!

350
00:26:27,787 --> 00:26:29,486
Don't screw this up.

351
00:26:30,655 --> 00:26:33,257
Aren't you even going to say hello?

352
00:26:35,627 --> 00:26:39,463
Oh, guys, you've got to see this.
Joker just spotted Harley!

353
00:26:43,635 --> 00:26:44,703
Keep walking.

354
00:26:44,704 --> 00:26:46,571
Tell him to shut up.

355
00:26:46,572 --> 00:26:50,342
Aw, I can tell you're still sore.

356
00:26:50,343 --> 00:26:53,410
At least the bruises
cleared up nicely.

357
00:26:56,247 --> 00:26:58,515
What's your hurry, Harl?

358
00:27:00,385 --> 00:27:02,519
Shut up! Shut up! Shut up!

359
00:27:04,289 --> 00:27:05,423
Damn it!

360
00:27:05,424 --> 00:27:07,292
(SIGHS) Let's move.

361
00:27:07,293 --> 00:27:08,860
(GUNSHOTS)

362
00:27:08,861 --> 00:27:11,229
Maybe, she'll kill him.

363
00:27:11,230 --> 00:27:13,865
I'm going to kill you!

364
00:27:13,866 --> 00:27:18,535
I'll kill him! I'll kill him
myself for what he's done to me!

365
00:27:24,809 --> 00:27:26,911
Women! Am I right, officer?

366
00:27:26,912 --> 00:27:30,447
Can't live with them, can't
kick them out of a moving car.

367
00:27:34,219 --> 00:27:37,355
You know the rules, buddy,
I got to phone it in.

368
00:27:37,356 --> 00:27:39,056
She's dead!

369
00:27:44,596 --> 00:27:46,665
How much trouble could she be?

370
00:27:46,666 --> 00:27:50,167
Nothing goes in or out of
Arkham without being okayed.

371
00:27:50,468 --> 00:27:52,470
But...

372
00:27:52,471 --> 00:27:56,073
Give me a sec, I'll try to get
a hold of the watch commander.

373
00:28:03,148 --> 00:28:04,382
Run it again.

374
00:28:04,383 --> 00:28:06,317
I tried twice, sir.

375
00:28:06,318 --> 00:28:09,419
I can't lose this job because
your system is down.

376
00:28:14,626 --> 00:28:16,927
Come on, you amateurs.

377
00:28:22,167 --> 00:28:25,669
(TUTTING) Sorry hon, bulletproof.

378
00:28:26,337 --> 00:28:29,940
Even better, puddin'.

379
00:28:37,949 --> 00:28:43,455
Why, Harley, if I didn't know better,
I'd say you're trying to kill me.

380
00:28:43,456 --> 00:28:45,724
We're finished, you and me!

381
00:28:45,725 --> 00:28:49,192
I got someone new
now, someone better!

382
00:28:49,794 --> 00:28:51,261
(GROWLING)

383
00:28:51,696 --> 00:28:53,465
Oh, hell!

384
00:28:53,466 --> 00:28:55,065
This will have to do.

385
00:29:00,071 --> 00:29:02,506
Never mind, just came through.

386
00:29:02,841 --> 00:29:04,308
About time!

387
00:29:12,684 --> 00:29:15,186
Sorry, it's an old system.

388
00:29:15,187 --> 00:29:16,954
No problem.

389
00:29:22,627 --> 00:29:25,095
Let's see what goodies we've got.

390
00:29:32,604 --> 00:29:34,338
Oh, shit!

391
00:29:49,788 --> 00:29:51,254
How the... ow!

392
00:29:53,858 --> 00:29:56,561
Ahh! My goolies!

393
00:29:56,562 --> 00:29:59,129
That's payback, you dumb ass.

394
00:30:00,498 --> 00:30:03,200
Walk it off, captain kangaroo.

395
00:30:38,770 --> 00:30:40,237
(GAS HISSING)

396
00:30:42,574 --> 00:30:44,409
Come on, we're out of time.

397
00:30:44,410 --> 00:30:45,577
New guy?

398
00:30:45,578 --> 00:30:48,745
That's right! You're
not jealous, are you?

399
00:30:50,348 --> 00:30:51,715
That's him!

400
00:30:53,384 --> 00:30:55,587
I know you.

401
00:30:55,588 --> 00:30:57,222
We worked together once.

402
00:30:57,223 --> 00:31:00,357
No, wait, don't tell me,
don't tell me. Hmm.

403
00:31:00,825 --> 00:31:03,827
Deadhead, hmm? Buckshot?

404
00:31:07,732 --> 00:31:09,267
(Harley SQUEALS)

405
00:31:09,268 --> 00:31:10,534
I got her!

406
00:31:11,402 --> 00:31:13,371
You can have her!

407
00:31:13,372 --> 00:31:16,573
Bet you buy your shirts
second hand too.

408
00:31:33,825 --> 00:31:36,461
Sir, we've got an
explosion on level E.

409
00:31:36,462 --> 00:31:38,129
He's still secure, sir.

410
00:31:38,130 --> 00:31:39,964
Is that room service?

411
00:31:39,965 --> 00:31:42,700
Tell them I never got my calzone.

412
00:31:42,701 --> 00:31:45,570
Good! I need every available
security down in the kitchen.

413
00:31:45,571 --> 00:31:46,704
Stat!

414
00:31:46,705 --> 00:31:48,238
We're on yellow alert.

415
00:31:48,873 --> 00:31:50,340
(ALL GROANING)

416
00:31:54,579 --> 00:31:55,780
You're late!

417
00:31:55,781 --> 00:31:58,381
Ran in to her ex. Grab hold!

418
00:32:00,285 --> 00:32:02,219
KING SHARK: Put your back into it.

419
00:32:06,591 --> 00:32:09,594
Hey! Nobody's supposed
to be down there!

420
00:32:09,595 --> 00:32:12,931
DEADSHOT: Ah, we just snuck
down here for a little party.

421
00:32:12,932 --> 00:32:14,598
(Harley GIGGLING)

422
00:32:15,667 --> 00:32:17,267
What kind of party?

423
00:32:19,637 --> 00:32:21,239
Crap! You're Harley Quinn!

424
00:32:21,240 --> 00:32:23,441
Don't move, you crazy bitch.

425
00:32:23,442 --> 00:32:24,708
(SCREAMS)

426
00:32:41,259 --> 00:32:42,493
Blech!

427
00:32:42,494 --> 00:32:44,494
I hate Italian food.

428
00:33:11,022 --> 00:33:13,191
Has that kitchen
fire been contained?

429
00:33:13,192 --> 00:33:15,358
- Yes, sir.
- (KNOCKING ON DOOR)

430
00:33:17,929 --> 00:33:19,396
Get here!

431
00:33:22,166 --> 00:33:24,369
- AMANDA: <i>Lawton!</i>
- What?

432
00:33:24,370 --> 00:33:27,205
<i>GPS has you in the
main security hub.</i>

433
00:33:27,206 --> 00:33:28,806
<i>What's going on?</i>

434
00:33:28,807 --> 00:33:30,241
We own it, that's what.

435
00:33:30,242 --> 00:33:32,176
Now we grab the cane.

436
00:33:32,177 --> 00:33:34,879
<i>Don't get to cocky, Lawton.
You're at the point of no return.</i>

437
00:33:34,880 --> 00:33:37,482
<i>You best keep that in mind.</i>

438
00:33:37,483 --> 00:33:40,585
That gas explosion put the whole
bloody asylum on yellow alert.

439
00:33:40,586 --> 00:33:43,154
If the security cameras
make us, we're toast.

440
00:33:43,155 --> 00:33:45,590
So shut down all the security cams.

441
00:33:45,591 --> 00:33:48,192
That's a sure fire way
to alert the bat.

442
00:33:48,193 --> 00:33:51,562
What then? Let him watch
us run around like idiots?

443
00:33:51,563 --> 00:33:53,797
KING SHARK:
Play yesterday's footage.

444
00:33:55,266 --> 00:33:57,902
Aw, shark-wick had
his first thought.

445
00:33:57,903 --> 00:34:00,638
Shut it, boomer! Say it again.

446
00:34:00,639 --> 00:34:03,508
Play yesterday's footage
of the same time.

447
00:34:03,509 --> 00:34:04,776
I can do that.

448
00:34:04,777 --> 00:34:06,911
And we can operate
without eyes on us.

449
00:34:06,912 --> 00:34:08,946
You mean Batman's or Waller's.

450
00:34:08,947 --> 00:34:10,580
Both!

451
00:34:13,184 --> 00:34:15,119
The intensive treatment
building is there,

452
00:34:15,120 --> 00:34:16,953
just across the yard.

453
00:34:17,522 --> 00:34:18,756
Let's move!

454
00:34:18,757 --> 00:34:20,557
Low profile.

455
00:34:22,093 --> 00:34:24,361
Frost, move your ass.

456
00:34:28,232 --> 00:34:30,300
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

457
00:34:38,876 --> 00:34:41,145
Top priority are those towers.

458
00:34:41,146 --> 00:34:42,747
I can scale them.

459
00:34:42,748 --> 00:34:44,014
No time.

460
00:34:56,360 --> 00:34:59,063
You do two, I'll do two.

461
00:34:59,064 --> 00:35:00,198
Fine!

462
00:35:00,199 --> 00:35:01,766
On my mark.

463
00:35:01,767 --> 00:35:03,033
Now!

464
00:35:09,740 --> 00:35:10,808
You missed!

465
00:35:10,809 --> 00:35:12,042
Wait for it.

466
00:35:14,679 --> 00:35:16,980
Patrol, I need a sweep of the yard!

467
00:35:20,885 --> 00:35:24,288
Boom! In your face!

468
00:35:24,289 --> 00:35:26,457
He got to his walky!
I'd score that a miss,

469
00:35:26,458 --> 00:35:28,526
you two-bit c-lister!

470
00:35:28,527 --> 00:35:30,128
That's it!

471
00:35:30,129 --> 00:35:31,594
(BOTH GRUNTING)

472
00:35:34,632 --> 00:35:38,202
U.S.A.! U.S.A.!

473
00:35:38,203 --> 00:35:40,570
Boys, we got company!

474
00:35:43,541 --> 00:35:44,842
Shark, no!

475
00:35:44,843 --> 00:35:47,444
Finally, some action!

476
00:35:48,813 --> 00:35:50,414
(MEN GROANING)

477
00:35:50,415 --> 00:35:52,783
So much for low profile.

478
00:35:52,784 --> 00:35:54,050
(Harley LAUGHING)

479
00:36:03,694 --> 00:36:05,263
Status report.

480
00:36:05,264 --> 00:36:08,465
I got you in the exercise yard, but
you don't show up on the cameras.

481
00:36:11,569 --> 00:36:14,338
Must be something wrong
with the system. Damn it!

482
00:36:14,339 --> 00:36:16,841
We're a little busy right now.

483
00:36:16,842 --> 00:36:18,509
I'll call you back.

484
00:36:18,510 --> 00:36:22,112
Don't yank me around, convict.
Get the cane, get out!

485
00:36:33,491 --> 00:36:35,024
Yahtzee.

486
00:36:39,130 --> 00:36:41,599
OFFICER: (THROUGH LOUDSPEAKER) <i>Victor
Zsasz, we've got you surrounded.</i>

487
00:36:41,600 --> 00:36:44,535
Please! Please, don't hurt me.

488
00:36:44,536 --> 00:36:46,837
<i>Let the girl go
before it gets ugly.</i>

489
00:36:46,838 --> 00:36:49,473
The zombie is mine to liberate.

490
00:36:49,474 --> 00:36:51,674
I have righteous work to do.

491
00:36:57,548 --> 00:37:00,183
I'm not in the mood tonight, Zsasz.

492
00:37:14,699 --> 00:37:16,968
<i>You seem troubled tonight, sir.</i>

493
00:37:16,969 --> 00:37:18,836
It's Harley, Alfred.

494
00:37:18,837 --> 00:37:21,439
She was acting odd.

495
00:37:21,440 --> 00:37:23,274
<i>Odder than usual, you mean.</i>

496
00:37:23,275 --> 00:37:26,043
Like she was happy to get caught.

497
00:37:26,044 --> 00:37:29,280
<i>Maybe she missed her puddin'?</i>

498
00:37:29,281 --> 00:37:30,681
Maybe.

499
00:37:30,682 --> 00:37:33,584
More likely it's linked
to the joker's bomb.

500
00:37:33,585 --> 00:37:36,520
Arkham had a yellow
alert this evening.

501
00:37:36,521 --> 00:37:38,922
<i>Everything looks to be in place.</i>

502
00:37:40,558 --> 00:37:42,059
Hmm.

503
00:37:42,060 --> 00:37:43,594
That's Mochel.

504
00:37:43,595 --> 00:37:46,464
He doesn't work Friday's.
Neither does Ferrick.

505
00:37:46,465 --> 00:37:48,065
That's the Thursday crew.

506
00:37:48,066 --> 00:37:51,035
This isn't live. They're
broadcasting old footage.

507
00:37:51,036 --> 00:37:53,204
Something's wrong at Arkham!

508
00:37:53,205 --> 00:37:54,804
(ENGINE REVVING)

509
00:38:01,245 --> 00:38:02,846
No! No!

510
00:38:04,048 --> 00:38:06,149
Enough, shark, put him down!

511
00:38:06,550 --> 00:38:07,817
Ow!

512
00:38:09,687 --> 00:38:10,954
Ouch!

513
00:38:12,056 --> 00:38:14,859
Do I have your attention now?

514
00:38:14,860 --> 00:38:18,228
Don't break cover in the middle
of an operation, unless I say so.

515
00:38:21,565 --> 00:38:24,602
Don't ever do that to me.

516
00:38:24,603 --> 00:38:27,170
Or what? You'll chew my head off?

517
00:38:28,172 --> 00:38:31,108
Do it! I'm begging you.

518
00:38:31,109 --> 00:38:35,111
You think any of you have a shot
of getting out alive without me?

519
00:38:38,983 --> 00:38:40,951
That's what I thought.

520
00:38:40,952 --> 00:38:43,220
We're just lucky
this was contained.

521
00:38:43,221 --> 00:38:45,690
Start following orders, all of you!

522
