00:59:47,984 --> 00:59:49,752
(PANTING)

794
00:59:49,753 --> 00:59:51,554
Why the hell are we running?

795
00:59:51,555 --> 00:59:52,889
We're sitting ducks here.

796
00:59:52,890 --> 00:59:56,059
And whose fault is that,
do you suppose, leader?

797
00:59:56,060 --> 00:59:58,928
I've been carrying this team
all night, you douche bag!

798
00:59:58,929 --> 01:00:00,597
- Ah, fellas!
- CAPTAIN BOOMERANG: Really?

799
01:00:00,598 --> 01:00:02,865
- Is that what you'd call it, eh?
- KILLER FROST: Guys.

800
01:00:02,866 --> 01:00:06,536
- Guys, listen...
- Yeah, yeah that's what I
call it, you one-gimmick hack.

801
01:00:06,537 --> 01:00:08,338
Great, let's split up.

802
01:00:08,339 --> 01:00:09,539
I'm better off on my own.

803
01:00:09,540 --> 01:00:11,840
Guys! Batman's here!

804
01:00:13,443 --> 01:00:15,712
Joker, where did he go?

805
01:00:15,713 --> 01:00:18,213
Don't owe you squat, bats!

806
01:00:23,386 --> 01:00:24,821
Lawton,

807
01:00:24,822 --> 01:00:26,856
we can settle our business later.

808
01:00:26,857 --> 01:00:28,890
Now, where's the joker?

809
01:00:30,159 --> 01:00:34,063
He and Harley took their
mallet and disappeared.

810
01:00:34,064 --> 01:00:36,699
That's where he's hidden the bomb.

811
01:00:36,700 --> 01:00:40,436
<i>Simulus testing! Simulus.</i>

812
01:00:40,437 --> 01:00:43,106
<i>I know you can see me, bats.</i>

813
01:00:43,107 --> 01:00:45,241
<i>Hope you brought protection.</i>

814
01:00:45,242 --> 01:00:49,012
<i>'Cause I'm about to give Gotham
a terminal case of tainted love</i>

815
01:00:49,013 --> 01:00:52,148
<i>and it's really gonna burn.</i>

816
01:00:52,149 --> 01:00:54,651
And just in case you're
thinking of stopping me,

817
01:00:54,652 --> 01:00:58,587
I figured I'd invite some
friends to my big blow-out.

818
01:01:26,616 --> 01:01:29,251
Stop! Please!

819
01:01:32,255 --> 01:01:34,257
(SCREAMING)

820
01:01:34,258 --> 01:01:37,259
I need to find joker
and stop that bomb.

821
01:01:38,861 --> 01:01:40,962
Good luck with that, mate.

822
01:01:43,666 --> 01:01:45,468
Got to get out of here.

823
01:01:45,469 --> 01:01:47,904
Yeah, but what will get us far
enough to escape that blast?

824
01:01:47,905 --> 01:01:49,404
(HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING)

825
01:01:58,581 --> 01:02:00,448
Well, isn't that convenient.

826
01:02:31,748 --> 01:02:33,214
(SHOUTING)

827
01:02:37,320 --> 01:02:38,621
Ow!

828
01:02:38,622 --> 01:02:40,155
Out of my way, loser.

829
01:02:48,397 --> 01:02:50,198
(OFFICERS SCREAMING)

830
01:03:05,081 --> 01:03:06,348
(GROANS)

831
01:03:10,286 --> 01:03:11,553
No!

832
01:03:19,896 --> 01:03:21,396
(KILLER FROST SCREAMS)

833
01:03:32,275 --> 01:03:35,210
Oh no you don't, Lawton.
That's my ride!

834
01:03:50,226 --> 01:03:51,627
(STRUGGLING)

835
01:03:51,628 --> 01:03:54,729
Only one of us is getting out
of here, and it ain't you!

836
01:03:56,766 --> 01:03:58,233
(SCREAMS)

837
01:04:00,770 --> 01:04:03,304
I'll get you for this, Lawton!

838
01:04:04,507 --> 01:04:06,341
Get those gates closed!

839
01:04:14,650 --> 01:04:16,384
Where's our backup?

840
01:04:49,185 --> 01:04:51,319
Now that's what I call backup.

841
01:05:23,686 --> 01:05:27,056
We've got it under control,
Batman, you can take...

842
01:05:27,057 --> 01:05:31,326
And I'm talking to myself, again.

843
01:05:40,670 --> 01:05:43,204
Going my way, handsome?

844
01:05:44,907 --> 01:05:46,409
Cute kid!

845
01:05:46,410 --> 01:05:49,911
Hope she doesn't take
being an orphan too hard?

846
01:05:53,883 --> 01:05:55,350
(GROANS)

847
01:06:12,401 --> 01:06:14,369
- (CONSOLE BEEPING)
- Huh?

848
01:06:20,943 --> 01:06:22,744
Holy crap!

849
01:06:40,262 --> 01:06:42,630
You know she's going
to kill us, right?

850
01:07:15,197 --> 01:07:17,565
Where's the fricking gas pedal?

851
01:07:50,733 --> 01:07:52,000
Uh-oh!

852
01:08:17,460 --> 01:08:20,229
Sure he smacks me around sometimes,

853
01:08:20,230 --> 01:08:22,731
but you're the one who's
always hurting me!

854
01:08:22,732 --> 01:08:25,033
Now I'm going to hurt you!

855
01:08:41,183 --> 01:08:43,084
Stop me, if you've heard this one.

856
01:08:51,927 --> 01:08:53,594
Listen to me!

857
01:08:55,297 --> 01:08:57,065
Harley, the bomb!

858
01:09:03,939 --> 01:09:05,406
(TICKING)

859
01:09:54,623 --> 01:09:57,458
For someone who's not Batman,

860
01:09:58,127 --> 01:10:01,596
you've been a real pain in my ass.

861
01:10:06,902 --> 01:10:09,103
Deuces, new guy!

862
01:10:20,282 --> 01:10:22,016
Have a seat, puddin'!

863
01:10:36,098 --> 01:10:37,565
Bang!

864
01:10:48,777 --> 01:10:50,178
(JOKER LAUGHING)

865
01:11:19,208 --> 01:11:21,143
BATMAN: Waller!

866
01:11:21,144 --> 01:11:24,480
You knew when you sent your
little suicide squad into Arkham,

867
01:11:24,481 --> 01:11:26,081
they'd go off script.

868
01:11:26,082 --> 01:11:28,250
Oh, it's just you.

869
01:11:28,251 --> 01:11:32,588
When your bombs didn't dice them,
you figured the SCU would.

870
01:11:32,589 --> 01:11:36,959
All that, just so you
could kill the riddler!

871
01:11:36,960 --> 01:11:40,496
Let's just say, I break a lot
of eggs to make an omelet.

872
01:11:40,497 --> 01:11:42,731
And because you're a messy cook,

873
01:11:42,732 --> 01:11:45,034
the riddler was able to escape.

874
01:11:45,035 --> 01:11:47,202
I got careless.

875
01:11:47,203 --> 01:11:49,505
My men will get Nigma next time.

876
01:11:49,506 --> 01:11:51,572
There is no next time.

877
01:11:51,774 --> 01:11:53,442
No?

878
01:11:53,443 --> 01:11:55,577
We're the U.S. government!

879
01:11:55,578 --> 01:11:58,380
Who's going to blow the
whistle on us, the convicts?

880
01:11:58,381 --> 01:12:00,015
Who'd believe them?

881
01:12:00,016 --> 01:12:01,483
You?

882
01:12:01,484 --> 01:12:04,086
You're going to start
a blog and expose us?

883
01:12:04,087 --> 01:12:05,920
I don't think so.

884
01:12:06,522 --> 01:12:09,590
That's checkmate, Batman.

885
01:12:11,727 --> 01:12:13,594
I'm warning you!

886
01:12:14,196 --> 01:12:16,031
Enough!

887
01:12:16,032 --> 01:12:19,935
Don't they need you back in
your squalid little city?

888
01:12:19,936 --> 01:12:23,304
They never did find the
joker's body, did they?

889
01:12:29,712 --> 01:12:30,978
Punk!

890
01:12:39,254 --> 01:12:40,988
Mother...

891
01:12:48,864 --> 01:12:50,064
Bang!